De Jager Says Won’t Decide on Greek Bondholder Losses for Now

-- B y   D a v i d   T w e e d
-- 
2011-10-04T11:35:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/de-jager-says-won-t-decide-on-greek-bondholder-losses-for-now.html
Dutch Finance Minister  Jan Kees de
Jager  said that the Netherlands won’t decide its position on the
involvement of private investors in the Greek bailout until the
Troika report has been published.  “After the report is out, we will direct our policy,” he
told journalists in Luxembourg today. “We have to wait for the
Troika.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Tweed in Tokyo at 
